Class Swing

  • java.lang.Object
    • Swing

  • public class Swing
extends java.lang.Object
    The Swing class acts as the GUI and has a nested private class to handle the textBox inputs to convert the [arabic, roman] to [roman, arabic].
    Since:
    SDK 1.8
    Author:
    Marc Shepherd

      Nested Classes

      private class  Swing.TextHandler
      The class private nested TextHandler acts as the helper for handling the inputs and outputs entered by the user.

      Swing()
      Constructs fields for each new object - Creates 4 new JTextFields, a handler to go with them, and adds the handlers to the input TextFields when enter is hit to respond to the action and convert to [roman, arabic].
